RACE.RACE_TEXT: Nebraska HBPA Stallion S. FONNER PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 80. Stakes Purse 14050. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE BEEN NOMINATED TO THE 2023 NEBRASKA HBPA STALLION STAKES. Weights: Three-year-olds 120 lbs.; Older 124 lbs.; Non-winners of $9,000 twice in 2022-2023 allowed 3 lbs.; Of $9,000 in 2022-2023, 5 lbs. Maiden, Claiming and Starter races not considered in allowances. High Weights Preferred, on the scale. Total earnings in 2022-23 will be used in determining the order of preference of horses being assigned equal weights. $50 to pass the entry box and an additional $50 t o start. Nomination fee $200 if paid by April 29th, 2023. A late supplemental nomination fee of $1,000 (includes entry & starting fees) due at time of entry. Closed Saturday, April 29 with seven nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RECORDER bided his time while saving ground through the opening two turns, moved closer while angling out going to the final turn, rallied four wide to loop the field in that bend and drew off under steady handling. G'S TURN tracked the leaders four wide, settled back going to the final turn then regained position in the lane as rivals weakened. BARSTOW stalked the pace three and four wide in good position but weakened into the lane. DEBONNAIRE DUDE contested the pace two to three wide outside a rival and weakened in the lane. FRIENDOFTHECOURT contested the pace inside rivals while out from the rail and weakened nearing the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Recorder
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, angled 4wd 5/16, looped field, drove clear

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 2 4F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 4700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DAVE dueled about the two path inside a rival early, kicked clear nearing the lane then held safe under steady handling. EXPECT ROYAL was never far back three and four wide, rallied but could not run down the winner. GRAYDAR'S DREAM dueled outside the winner early and lacked a final closing run. JUST RIGHT MIKE was in reach three wide but lacked a closing bid. DRYSPELL angled four wide nearing the lane but lacked a rally. CHILLY WILLIS was outrun.

ENTRY.NAME: Dave
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled, kicked clear, held safe thru lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 3 4F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 6300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE NOVEMBER 12, 2022. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OGA BEAR showed speed inside a rival to kick clear through the turn and drew off under an energetic hand ride. CHERUBIM chased the pace three wide and gained clear for the place while no match for the winner. THE GRAY DEHERE was three wide to move up in the lane but lacked a solid closing bid. GETALOADOFTHIS challenged the winner from outside to the turn and weakened in the lane. SUBSCRIPTION failed to mount a bid four wide. SOUTHERN SMOKE saved ground and lacked a rally.

ENTRY.COMMENT: 3wd, no match winner, clear for place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 5300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOUBLETROUBLE BEAR was on the pace about the two to three path to kick clear into the far turn, shook off a bid turning for home and held safe to the end. BRADSTREET tracked the pace three and four wide to bid outside the winner turning for home but could not run that one down. STAR OF STARS stalked the pace three wide, moved in through the far turn but could not close on the top pair. AFTER BURN briefly contested the pace inside the winner and dropped back after a half. HESACALENDARBOY saved ground and had no rally. GREAT REALIZATION was always back. SCOOTER FLASH was outrun and lost contact with the field going to the final turn.
